<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10284&amp;p=135312#p135312"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: community fonts for NES Dev]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10284&amp;p=135312#p135312"><![CDATA[
Here's an <a href="http://fontstruct.com/fontstructions/show/919913" class="postlink">8x8 monospaced font</a> I call SDS 8x8! The SDS stands for Super Dragonsin Saga, which is the project I originally made this for.<br /><br />It's a multi-purpose font I made years ago and I've slowly honed it to perfection over the years as I've used it for my projects. If you want to add this font to a CHR page, I suggest you download it and manually type it into a 128x128 image. This method works well and allows for a lot of flexibility as far as the arrangement of tiles.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6734">DragonDePlatino</a> — Tue Oct 21, 2014 2:33 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
