<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: community fonts for NES Dev]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10284&amp;p=117015#p117015"><![CDATA[
Can I make request? If so, this is a request for the following font (if someone is good to make such a font):<ul><li>Fix pitch 8x8</li><li>Using color 1 for background and 2 for foreground, not color 0 and 3</li><li>ASCII characters 0x20 to 0x5F are in their places.</li><li>The uppercase letters are duplicated in the positions of lowercase</li><li>One of the unused slots will then be filled in with the cursor icon, which uses color 3 for foreground (so that it can blink)</li><li>Looks fine if used as a font for a text adventure game in all uppercase</li><li>The 0x80 to 0xFF are like 0x00 to 0x7F but are distinguished from the main ones, such as: reverse video, or bold, or italic, or something else</li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4734">zzo38</a> — Sat Aug 24, 2013 3:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
